<subSubSection pageId="8" pageNumber="509" type="description">
<paragraph blockId="8.[151,1437,511,1653]" pageId="8" pageNumber="509">
<emphasis bold="true" box="[199,382,763,789]" pageId="8" pageNumber="509">Measurements.</emphasis>
Total length 13.1–14.5; total width 6.9–7.9; head length 2.9–3.2; head width 2.9–3.2; interocular distance: 1.6–1.7; length of antennal articles I: 0.6–0,9; II: 0.9–1.0; III: 1.2–1.5; IV: 2.5–2.9; V: 2.8–3.0; pronotum length 2.5–3.0; pronotum width 9.2–10.1; scutellum length 6.0–6.7; scutellum width 4.5–5,3.
</paragraph>
</subSubSection>
<subSubSection pageId="8" pageNumber="509" type="diagnosis">
<paragraph blockId="8.[151,1437,511,1653]" pageId="8" pageNumber="509">
<emphasis bold="true" box="[199,322,870,896]" pageId="8" pageNumber="509">Diagnosis.</emphasis>
Antennomeres with increasing lengths progressively (I&lt;II&lt;III&lt;IV≤V). Anterolateral margin of pronotum unpunctured (
<figureCitation box="[424,528,907,933]" captionStart="FIGURE 11" captionStartId="16.[151,250,1899,1923]" captionTargetBox="[321,1260,659,1832]" captionTargetId="figure-155@16.[151,1435,622,1874]" captionTargetPageId="16" captionText="FIGURE 11. Dorsal and ventral view. A–B H. curvatus sp. n.; C–D Hypoxys ocanensis sp. n. Scale bars = 5mm." figureDoi="http://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.6911536" httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/6911536/files/figure.png" pageId="8" pageNumber="509">Fig. 11A</figureCitation>
). Humeral angles posteriorly curved, longer than eyes width (
<figureCitation box="[1226,1330,907,933]" captionStart="FIGURE 11" captionStartId="16.[151,250,1899,1923]" captionTargetBox="[321,1260,659,1832]" captionTargetId="figure-155@16.[151,1435,622,1874]" captionTargetPageId="16" captionText="FIGURE 11. Dorsal and ventral view. A–B H. curvatus sp. n.; C–D Hypoxys ocanensis sp. n. Scale bars = 5mm." figureDoi="http://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.6911536" httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/6911536/files/figure.png" pageId="8" pageNumber="509">Fig. 11A</figureCitation>
). Corium reddish brown (
<figureCitation box="[323,425,943,969]" captionStart="FIGURE 11" captionStartId="16.[151,250,1899,1923]" captionTargetBox="[321,1260,659,1832]" captionTargetId="figure-155@16.[151,1435,622,1874]" captionTargetPageId="16" captionText="FIGURE 11. Dorsal and ventral view. A–B H. curvatus sp. n.; C–D Hypoxys ocanensis sp. n. Scale bars = 5mm." figureDoi="http://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.6911536" httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/6911536/files/figure.png" pageId="8" pageNumber="509">Fig. 11A</figureCitation>
). Metasternal process with arms of anterior bifurcation receiving 2/3 of third rostral segment (
<figureCitation box="[159,260,979,1005]" captionStart="FIGURE 11" captionStartId="16.[151,250,1899,1923]" captionTargetBox="[321,1260,659,1832]" captionTargetId="figure-155@16.[151,1435,622,1874]" captionTargetPageId="16" captionText="FIGURE 11. Dorsal and ventral view. A–B H. curvatus sp. n.; C–D Hypoxys ocanensis sp. n. Scale bars = 5mm." figureDoi="http://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.6911536" httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/6911536/files/figure.png" pageId="8" pageNumber="509">Fig. 11B</figureCitation>
). Pseudosutures of abdomen with adjacent dark green spot (
<figureCitation box="[920,1020,979,1005]" captionStart="FIGURE 11" captionStartId="16.[151,250,1899,1923]" captionTargetBox="[321,1260,659,1832]" captionTargetId="figure-155@16.[151,1435,622,1874]" captionTargetPageId="16" captionText="FIGURE 11. Dorsal and ventral view. A–B H. curvatus sp. n.; C–D Hypoxys ocanensis sp. n. Scale bars = 5mm." figureDoi="http://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.6911536" httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/6911536/files/figure.png" pageId="8" pageNumber="509">Fig. 11B</figureCitation>
). 
<emphasis bold="true" box="[1038,1207,978,1005]" pageId="8" pageNumber="509">Male genitalia</emphasis>
. Dorsal surface with spot restricted to coarse area of the pygophore (
<figureCitation box="[700,793,1015,1041]" captionStart="FIGURE 4" captionStartId="9.[151,250,1895,1919]" captionTargetBox="[201,1400,209,1833]" captionTargetId="figure-17@9.[151,1435,181,1871]" captionTargetPageId="9" captionText="FIGURE 4. Hypoxys curvatus sp. n. Male (pygophore):A—dorsal view, B —posterior view, C—ventral view, D—posterolateral view. Female: E—genital plates. Scale bars = 1 mm." figureDoi="http://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.6911514" httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/6911514/files/figure.png" pageId="8" pageNumber="509">Fig. 4A</figureCitation>
). Dorsal rim less excavated than other species (
<figureCitation box="[1340,1424,1015,1041]" captionStart="FIGURE 4" captionStartId="9.[151,250,1895,1919]" captionTargetBox="[201,1400,209,1833]" captionTargetId="figure-17@9.[151,1435,181,1871]" captionTargetPageId="9" captionText="FIGURE 4. Hypoxys curvatus sp. n. Male (pygophore):A—dorsal view, B —posterior view, C—ventral view, D—posterolateral view. Female: E—genital plates. Scale bars = 1 mm." figureDoi="http://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.6911514" httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/6911514/files/figure.png" pageId="8" pageNumber="509">Fig.4A</figureCitation>
); lateral expansion slightly surpassing level of posterolateral angles (
<figureCitation box="[922,1013,1051,1077]" captionStart="FIGURE 4" captionStartId="9.[151,250,1895,1919]" captionTargetBox="[201,1400,209,1833]" captionTargetId="figure-17@9.[151,1435,181,1871]" captionTargetPageId="9" captionText="FIGURE 4. Hypoxys curvatus sp. n. Male (pygophore):A—dorsal view, B —posterior view, C—ventral view, D—posterolateral view. Female: E—genital plates. Scale bars = 1 mm." figureDoi="http://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.6911514" httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/6911514/files/figure.png" pageId="8" pageNumber="509">Fig. 4C</figureCitation>
). Superior process of the genital cup elliptic, long and narrow (
<figureCitation box="[439,527,1087,1113]" captionStart="FIGURE 4" captionStartId="9.[151,250,1895,1919]" captionTargetBox="[201,1400,209,1833]" captionTargetId="figure-17@9.[151,1435,181,1871]" captionTargetPageId="9" captionText="FIGURE 4. Hypoxys curvatus sp. n. Male (pygophore):A—dorsal view, B —posterior view, C—ventral view, D—posterolateral view. Female: E—genital plates. Scale bars = 1 mm." figureDoi="http://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.6911514" httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/6911514/files/figure.png" pageId="8" pageNumber="509">Fig. 4B</figureCitation>
). Paramere head with distal margin strongly concave; anterior and posterior lobes subrectangular, apices rounded; anterior lobe large, reaching the superior process of the genital cup; posterior lobe short and laterally curved (
<figureCitation box="[457,549,1159,1185]" captionStart="FIGURE 4" captionStartId="9.[151,250,1895,1919]" captionTargetBox="[201,1400,209,1833]" captionTargetId="figure-17@9.[151,1435,181,1871]" captionTargetPageId="9" captionText="FIGURE 4. Hypoxys curvatus sp. n. Male (pygophore):A—dorsal view, B —posterior view, C—ventral view, D—posterolateral view. Female: E—genital plates. Scale bars = 1 mm." figureDoi="http://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.6911514" httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/6911514/files/figure.png" pageId="8" pageNumber="509">Fig. 4D</figureCitation>
). Proctiger moderately excavated laterally, excavation covered by short sparse setae; posterior face triangular (
<figureCitation box="[512,602,1195,1221]" captionStart="FIGURE 4" captionStartId="9.[151,250,1895,1919]" captionTargetBox="[201,1400,209,1833]" captionTargetId="figure-17@9.[151,1435,181,1871]" captionTargetPageId="9" captionText="FIGURE 4. Hypoxys curvatus sp. n. Male (pygophore):A—dorsal view, B —posterior view, C—ventral view, D—posterolateral view. Female: E—genital plates. Scale bars = 1 mm." figureDoi="http://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.6911514" httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/6911514/files/figure.png" pageId="8" pageNumber="509">Fig. 4B</figureCitation>
). Inner wall with slight swollen, narrow area contiguous to posterolateral angles (
<figureCitation box="[240,327,1231,1257]" captionStart="FIGURE 8" captionStartId="13.[151,250,1859,1883]" captionTargetBox="[250,1339,204,1800]" captionTargetId="figure-17@13.[199,1389,181,1835]" captionTargetPageId="13" captionText="FIGURE 8. Male genital capsule in posterolateral view, swollen area on inner wall of the pygophore indicated by the arrow: A—Hypoxys triangularis; B—H. capito; C—H. subrastratus; D—H. myrtacivorus sp. n.; E—H. curvatus sp. n.; F—H. striatus sp. n. Scale bars = 1mm." figureDoi="http://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.6911526" httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/6911526/files/figure.png" pageId="8" pageNumber="509">Fig. 8E</figureCitation>
, black arrow). Ventral rim excavated, V-shaped; expansions little developed, rounded and curved dorsally (
<figureCitation box="[258,349,1267,1293]" captionStart="FIGURE 4" captionStartId="9.[151,250,1895,1919]" captionTargetBox="[201,1400,209,1833]" captionTargetId="figure-17@9.[151,1435,181,1871]" captionTargetPageId="9" captionText="FIGURE 4. Hypoxys curvatus sp. n. Male (pygophore):A—dorsal view, B —posterior view, C—ventral view, D—posterolateral view. Female: E—genital plates. Scale bars = 1 mm." figureDoi="http://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.6911514" httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/6911514/files/figure.png" pageId="8" pageNumber="509">Fig. 4C</figureCitation>
). 
<emphasis bold="true" box="[370,568,1266,1293]" pageId="8" pageNumber="509">Female genitalia</emphasis>
(
<figureCitation box="[585,674,1267,1293]" captionStart="FIGURE 4" captionStartId="9.[151,250,1895,1919]" captionTargetBox="[201,1400,209,1833]" captionTargetId="figure-17@9.[151,1435,181,1871]" captionTargetPageId="9" captionText="FIGURE 4. Hypoxys curvatus sp. n. Male (pygophore):A—dorsal view, B —posterior view, C—ventral view, D—posterolateral view. Female: E—genital plates. Scale bars = 1 mm." figureDoi="http://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.6911514" httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/6911514/files/figure.png" pageId="8" pageNumber="509">Fig. 4E</figureCitation>
). Valvifers VIII distal and outer lateral margins almost straight and sloping; outer angle of the posterior margin forming a spine overlapping valvifers IX base (
<figureCitation box="[1207,1295,1303,1329]" captionStart="FIGURE 9" captionStartId="14.[151,250,1838,1862]" captionTargetBox="[247,1354,212,1787]" captionTargetId="figure-25@14.[199,1389,181,1814]" captionTargetPageId="14" captionText="FIGURE 9. Female genital plates in oblique view, mediolateral crest swollen on valvifers VIII indicated by the arrow: A— Hypoxys triangularis; B—H. capito; C—H. subrastratus; D—H. myrtacivorus sp. n.; E—H. curvatus sp. n.; F—H. striatus sp. n. Scale bars = 1mm." figureDoi="http://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.6911528" httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/6911528/files/figure.png" pageId="8" pageNumber="509">Fig. 9E</figureCitation>
, red arrow); mediolateral crest swollen globose (
<figureCitation box="[552,637,1339,1365]" captionStart="FIGURE 9" captionStartId="14.[151,250,1838,1862]" captionTargetBox="[247,1354,212,1787]" captionTargetId="figure-25@14.[199,1389,181,1814]" captionTargetPageId="14" captionText="FIGURE 9. Female genital plates in oblique view, mediolateral crest swollen on valvifers VIII indicated by the arrow: A— Hypoxys triangularis; B—H. capito; C—H. subrastratus; D—H. myrtacivorus sp. n.; E—H. curvatus sp. n.; F—H. striatus sp. n. Scale bars = 1mm." figureDoi="http://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.6911528" httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/6911528/files/figure.png" pageId="8" pageNumber="509">Fig. 9E</figureCitation>
, black arrow); mesial borders with deep U-shaped excavation. Valvulae IX exposed, with median keel, and somewhat sclerotized.
</paragraph>
</subSubSection>
