<subSubSection pageId="8" pageNumber="509" type="discussion">
<paragraph blockId="8.[151,1437,511,1653]" pageId="8" pageNumber="509">
<emphasis bold="true" box="[199,335,1446,1472]" pageId="8" pageNumber="509">Comments.</emphasis>
The female genitalia of 
<taxonomicName authority="Cunha &amp; Fernandes, 2022" authorityName="Cunha &amp; Fernandes" authorityYear="2022" box="[621,754,1447,1472]" class="Insecta" family="Pentatomidae" genus="Hypoxys" higherTaxonomySource="GBIF" kingdom="Animalia" order="Hemiptera" pageId="8" pageNumber="509" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="curvatus" status="sp. n.">
<emphasis box="[621,754,1447,1472]" italics="true" pageId="8" pageNumber="509">H. curvatus</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
<emphasis bold="true" box="[764,830,1447,1473]" pageId="8" pageNumber="509">
<taxonomicNameLabel box="[764,830,1447,1473]" pageId="8" pageNumber="509" rank="species">sp. n.</taxonomicNameLabel>
</emphasis>
, 
<taxonomicName authority="Cunha &amp; Fernandes, 2022" authorityName="Cunha &amp; Fernandes" authorityYear="2022" box="[846,1030,1447,1472]" class="Insecta" family="Pentatomidae" genus="Hypoxys" higherTaxonomySource="GBIF" kingdom="Animalia" order="Hemiptera" pageId="8" pageNumber="509" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="myrtacivorus" status="sp. n.">
<emphasis box="[846,1030,1447,1472]" italics="true" pageId="8" pageNumber="509">H. myrtacivorus</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
<emphasis bold="true" box="[1039,1105,1447,1473]" pageId="8" pageNumber="509">
<taxonomicNameLabel box="[1039,1105,1447,1473]" pageId="8" pageNumber="509" rank="species">sp. n.</taxonomicNameLabel>
</emphasis>
, 
<taxonomicName authority="Cunha &amp; Fernandes, 2022" authorityName="Cunha &amp; Fernandes" authorityYear="2022" box="[1121,1268,1447,1472]" class="Insecta" family="Pentatomidae" genus="Hypoxys" higherTaxonomySource="GBIF" kingdom="Animalia" order="Hemiptera" pageId="8" pageNumber="509" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="ocanensis" status="sp. n.">
<emphasis box="[1121,1268,1447,1472]" italics="true" pageId="8" pageNumber="509">H. ocanensis</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
<emphasis bold="true" box="[1277,1343,1447,1473]" pageId="8" pageNumber="509">
<taxonomicNameLabel box="[1277,1343,1447,1473]" pageId="8" pageNumber="509" rank="species">sp. n.</taxonomicNameLabel>
</emphasis>
, and 
<taxonomicName authorityName="Nunes et al." authorityYear="2020" baseAuthorityName="Dallas" baseAuthorityYear="1851" class="Insecta" family="Pentatomidae" genus="Hypoxys" higherTaxonomySource="GBIF" kingdom="Animalia" order="Hemiptera" pageId="8" pageNumber="509" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="triangularis">
<emphasis italics="true" pageId="8" pageNumber="509">H. triangularis</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
show the outer angle forming a spine, but in 
<taxonomicName authority="Cunha &amp; Fernandes, 2022" authorityName="Cunha &amp; Fernandes" authorityYear="2022" box="[809,941,1483,1508]" class="Insecta" family="Pentatomidae" genus="Hypoxys" higherTaxonomySource="GBIF" kingdom="Animalia" order="Hemiptera" pageId="8" pageNumber="509" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="curvatus" status="sp. n.">
<emphasis box="[809,941,1483,1508]" italics="true" pageId="8" pageNumber="509">H. curvatus</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
<emphasis bold="true" box="[950,1015,1483,1509]" pageId="8" pageNumber="509">
<taxonomicNameLabel box="[950,1015,1483,1509]" pageId="8" pageNumber="509" rank="species">sp. n.</taxonomicNameLabel>
</emphasis>
and 
<taxonomicName authority="Cunha &amp; Fernandes, 2022" authorityName="Cunha &amp; Fernandes" authorityYear="2022" box="[1072,1218,1483,1508]" class="Insecta" family="Pentatomidae" genus="Hypoxys" higherTaxonomySource="GBIF" kingdom="Animalia" order="Hemiptera" pageId="8" pageNumber="509" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="ocanensis" status="sp. n.">
<emphasis box="[1072,1218,1483,1508]" italics="true" pageId="8" pageNumber="509">H. ocanensis</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
<emphasis bold="true" box="[1227,1293,1483,1509]" pageId="8" pageNumber="509">
<taxonomicNameLabel box="[1227,1293,1483,1509]" pageId="8" pageNumber="509" rank="species">sp. n.</taxonomicNameLabel>
</emphasis>
this spine is dislocated to the middle of the valvifers IX base (in 
<taxonomicName authority="Cunha &amp; Fernandes, 2022" authorityName="Cunha &amp; Fernandes" authorityYear="2022" box="[741,924,1519,1544]" class="Insecta" family="Pentatomidae" genus="Hypoxys" higherTaxonomySource="GBIF" kingdom="Animalia" order="Hemiptera" pageId="8" pageNumber="509" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="myrtacivorus" status="sp. n.">
<emphasis box="[741,924,1519,1544]" italics="true" pageId="8" pageNumber="509">H. myrtacivorus</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
<emphasis bold="true" box="[931,996,1519,1545]" pageId="8" pageNumber="509">
<taxonomicNameLabel box="[931,996,1519,1545]" pageId="8" pageNumber="509" rank="species">sp. n.</taxonomicNameLabel>
</emphasis>
(
<figureCitation box="[1011,1095,1519,1545]" captionStart="FIGURE 1" captionStartId="4.[151,250,1905,1929]" captionTargetBox="[182,1399,216,1846]" captionTargetId="figure-25@4.[151,1435,181,1881]" captionTargetPageId="4" captionText="FIGURE 1. Hypoxys myrtacivorus sp. n. Male (pygophore): A—dorsal view, B —posterior view, C—ventral view, D— posterolateral view. Female: E—genital plates. Acronyms: Dr—dorsal rim; Pc—superior process of the genital cup; Pa— parameres; Proc—proctiger; Vr—ventral rim; Vf8—valvifers VIII; Vf9—valvifers IX; Lat 8—laterotergites VIII; Lat 9— laterotergites IX; Va9—valvulae IX; X—tenth segment. Scale bars = 1 mm." figureDoi="http://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.6911505" httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/6911505/files/figure.png" pageId="8" pageNumber="509">Fig. 1E</figureCitation>
) and 
<taxonomicName authorityName="Nunes et al." authorityYear="2020" baseAuthorityName="Dallas" baseAuthorityYear="1851" box="[1160,1329,1519,1545]" class="Insecta" family="Pentatomidae" genus="Hypoxys" higherTaxonomySource="GBIF" kingdom="Animalia" order="Hemiptera" pageId="8" pageNumber="509" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="triangularis">
<emphasis box="[1160,1329,1519,1545]" italics="true" pageId="8" pageNumber="509">H. triangularis</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
the outer angle spine is lateral). 
<taxonomicName authority="Cunha &amp; Fernandes, 2022" authorityName="Cunha &amp; Fernandes" authorityYear="2022" box="[415,617,1555,1580]" class="Insecta" family="Pentatomidae" genus="Hypoxys" higherTaxonomySource="GBIF" kingdom="Animalia" order="Hemiptera" pageId="8" pageNumber="509" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="curvatus" status="sp. n.">
<emphasis box="[415,617,1555,1580]" italics="true" pageId="8" pageNumber="509">Hypoxys curvatus</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
<emphasis bold="true" box="[627,693,1555,1581]" pageId="8" pageNumber="509">
<taxonomicNameLabel box="[627,693,1555,1581]" pageId="8" pageNumber="509" rank="species">sp. n.</taxonomicNameLabel>
</emphasis>
can be separated from 
<taxonomicName authority="Cunha &amp; Fernandes, 2022" authorityName="Cunha &amp; Fernandes" authorityYear="2022" box="[966,1113,1555,1580]" class="Insecta" family="Pentatomidae" genus="Hypoxys" higherTaxonomySource="GBIF" kingdom="Animalia" order="Hemiptera" pageId="8" pageNumber="509" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="ocanensis" status="sp. n.">
<emphasis box="[966,1113,1555,1580]" italics="true" pageId="8" pageNumber="509">H. ocanensis</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
<emphasis bold="true" box="[1123,1190,1555,1581]" pageId="8" pageNumber="509">
<taxonomicNameLabel box="[1123,1190,1555,1581]" pageId="8" pageNumber="509" rank="species">sp. n.</taxonomicNameLabel>
</emphasis>
by mesial borders of valvifers VIII deeply excavated and U-shaped (less excavated and V-shaped in 
<taxonomicName authority="Cunha &amp; Fernandes, 2022" authorityName="Cunha &amp; Fernandes" authorityYear="2022" box="[1056,1202,1591,1616]" class="Insecta" family="Pentatomidae" genus="Hypoxys" higherTaxonomySource="GBIF" kingdom="Animalia" order="Hemiptera" pageId="8" pageNumber="509" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="ocanensis" status="sp. n.">
<emphasis box="[1056,1202,1591,1616]" italics="true" pageId="8" pageNumber="509">H. ocanensis</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
<emphasis bold="true" box="[1211,1276,1591,1617]" pageId="8" pageNumber="509">
<taxonomicNameLabel box="[1211,1276,1591,1617]" pageId="8" pageNumber="509" rank="species">sp. n.</taxonomicNameLabel>
</emphasis>
). The spinose outer angle separates these four species from the others of 
<taxonomicName authorityName="Nunes et al." authorityYear="2020" baseAuthorityName="Dallas" baseAuthorityYear="1851" box="[807,980,1626,1653]" class="Insecta" family="Pentatomidae" genus="Hypoxys" higherTaxonomySource="GBIF" kingdom="Animalia" order="Hemiptera" pageId="8" pageNumber="509" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="triangularis">
<emphasis bold="true" box="[807,980,1626,1653]" italics="true" pageId="8" pageNumber="509">H. triangularis</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
group.
</paragraph>
</subSubSection>
